5. Order Cancellation & Product Return Policy

Non-returnable products include bioCERTIFIED™ and compendia chemicals (USP, EP, JP, NF, FCC), controlled substances, temperature-sensitive products, sterile products and other special order products such as certain items not traditionally stocked in Spectrum warehouses. Bulk orders (products designated with a “BL” at the end of the catalog number) and transactions with change control catalog numbers (designated with a “YY”) may not be cancelled once ordered. Products that have already shipped from our facility or are in staged/picked status may not be cancelled. In the event that product is not available in a timely manner as determined by Spectrum, cancellation requests will be considered on a case-by-case basis.

Returned items are subject to a minimum 25% restocking fee plus return shipping fees. Requests to return products must be made within 15 days of receipt for U.S. orders and within 30 days for international shipments. For returnable items, contact Customer Service to request a Return Materials Authorization (RMA) number. All returns must be packed in the original packaging and labeled in accordance with U.S. Department of Transportation (DOT) regulations applying to transportation of hazardous materials and in a manner that will preserve the product from any damage. To ensure prompt handling, the return authorization number should be placed on the outside of the package and a detailed explanation of the defect enclosed with the product.

Credits are not offered after products are returned without prior written consent by Spectrum.
